<!channel>: Hey team. Droga needs to bump the creative session again.
Andy did just forward a deck with a couple ideas though. Posting that to basecamp in a moment.
I read through the deck, those are pretty cute ideas

from a code standpoint, we would need to use pinch or choreograph the user positioning devices. We can know the current device orientation, but I don't think we can know that your Android is to the right of my Android.
Also, these ideas look like all the "pieces" are specific bits of content that dictate their own position and orientation. (monster eyes for example)
Also, a travel update: no travel this Sunday, and probably not early next week. Looks like we'll be waiting until the full SOW is approved
